{
  "stem": "19550.8",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 208.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we all agreed that whoever of us survives, that is going to be the meeting place for us.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And so when I grabbed the first American soldier, and wrote, and told him to advise my father that I'm alive.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I would say that it took no more than maybe a week or 10 days when he turned to me.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And incidentally, in honor of this soldiers, Private [?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Barrant, ?] who my sister and I have rediscovered maybe about two years ago, and who has since died-- it should, I should say that he went about Germany buttonholing survivors and asking them whether they had relatives, or friends, or anybody that they wished to notify through him of their survival.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "This was his way of trying to help the survivors.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Anyway, within about 7 to 10 days, he sought me out, I think still in the hospital in Tutzing, and brought back a letter from my father and two of my sisters who wrote me with the, in their own handwriting.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And this was an almost unbelievable occurrence.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "When the survivors heard of it, again, the same kind of hope welled up in the minds of a lot of people.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Listen, if Phillip has three sisters already in America, well only, we were only liberated 10 days ago.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It must be that a lot of, if not all, of our women and families have survived.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was liberated on V-E Day, which officially was May 8.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were really I think liberated probably after the surrender was signed by Admiral Donitz, a few hours after that.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then as I started to say, I went to Feldafing and--",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
